description: Roberto Guimarães has had Renard Lecombe, Mister No’s customer, kidnapped and now he’s threatening to kill him. To save him, Jerry will have to enter into an alliance with an unscrupulous blackguard: Paco “Fera”, the beast. Amid fast-pace pursuits, shoot-outs and murderous attacks, the nights of Recife become the arena of a deadly sparring match!
name: Corsa Contro il Tempo

description: A new prophet! The Taulipang indios think they have identified him in a strange individual who says he comes from the future and talks about extraordinary adventures. However, Mister No seems to be the only one capable of understanding the incredible stories of the “Sacred Man”, and that’s why the indios have to capture the pilot and force him to cooperate with them. But what secrets are really hidden in the world evoked by the unknown individual?
name: L'Uomo del Futuro

description: When the members of the “Cartel” he belongs to kill his son Paulo, Alberto Alvez sets in motion a a vicious plan of revenge: he will throw himself on the mercy of the CIA and squeal, disclosing all the criminal dealings of the mob family he is part of. But none of his ex colleagues will get to a trial alive: Alvez, thirsting for blood, is going to murder them one by one!
name: Il Pentito

description: Things are moving fast in “supergrass” Alvez’s plan to punish the perpetrators and masterminds who are behind the death of his son Paulo. Not only does he intend to squeal to the CIA all sorts of goings-on and wrongdoings of the crime family he belonged to, but he’s also determined to continue his transformation into judge and executioner, eliminating his one-time crime partners one by one. It’s going to be up to Mister No to put an end to a long trail of blood…
name: Trappola per Topi

description: In 1934, a postal service aeroplane with the celebrated writer and aviation pioneer Antoine de Saint-Exupéry sitting at the controls crashes into the Amazon jungle. Many years later a French pilot, a real friendly guy called Marcel Brest, persuades Mister No and Esse-Esse to set off with him in search of the wreckage of that ancient aircraft, which was carrying a package that contained “something” extremely precious…
name: Il Tesoro di Saint-Exupéry

description: Someone else is interested in the precious content of the aircraft that was in charge of with the mail delivery when, in 1934, it crashed into the tangled green undergrowth of the Amazon forest. It seems that someone has followed Marcel Brest’s investigations over the years and now the lives of both the French pilot and Mister No are at risk. But what does Antoine de Saint-Exupéry’s plane really conceal?
name: Minaccia dal Passato

description: Forced by a mechanical fault affecting his piper to attempt a hazardous emergency landing, Mister No finds himself in the midst of a tribe of indios who live hidden inside a huge cave. The indios believe they are the guardians of the “Tears of god”, extremely precious nuggets of gold destined to set loose a whole load of trouble when their existence is discovered by a group of unscrupulous garimpeiros!
name: Atterraggio Forzato

description: The garimpeiros who are hunting for the indios’ gold are sailing upriver and are inevitably bound to discover the hiding place where the “Little People” have taken cover. And there are unscrupulous men around who have no qualms about exterminating all of the indios for the purpose of getting their hands on those precious nuggets. Only Mister No can save the situation, with the aid of a group of men from the military. But the gringo is going to have to muster up all his cunning and for the umpteenth time put his own life on the line in a sparring match where a fundamental role will be played by an unexpected traitor!
name: Il Marchio del Traditore

description: This is the beginning of the long-drawn-out adventure that’s destined to change Jerry Drake’s life for ever. Mister No, in the early 1970s, goes back to his Manaus and finds himself confronted with a new, unexpected situation. Because at that time, both the Amazonian region and also the whole of Brazil are in the throes of a devastating economic and socio-political upheaval…
name: Qualcosa È Cambiato

description: Here’s what the new Manaus is like: full of factories, new buildings and crowded shops, and invaded by throngs of people looking for work. This is hard for Jerry Drake to stomach. But the worst surprises come from a trip into the jungle. What happens, you see, is that when he tries to help two apparently innocuous kids by giving them a ride in his Piper, this turns out to be just the beginning of a dramatic adventure…
name: Uno Strano Appuntamento

description: Several young idealists turn self-styled warriors, but their dream of justice and freedom is doomed to clash with the harsh reality of life in the Amazons. And while a corner of paradise risks being transformed into a veritable hell, Mister No, caught in the cross-fire, has to fight to save his own skin!
name: Il Fuoco e il Sangue

description: Stelio, the jangadeiro of Pecèm, has effectively moved to Manaus, abandoning the Atlantic coasts in favor of working in a factory buried deep in the jungle, so as to guarantee the survival of his family who live so far away. But in the new Amazonian city, where metal and concrete increasingly appear to mushroom almost overnight all over the place, survival is really one hell of a task. And so it falls to Mister No to help his friend avoid falling prey to the paradise of illusions called Ayahuasca!
name: Ayahuasca

description: Mister No is fighting a race against time: his friend Stelio is becoming possessed by a ghastly nightmare, and can’t seem to wake up from it. It’s Ayahuasca, the powerful hallucinogenic drug, that’s holding him prisoner. During the pitch-black Manaus night, flames transform the Casa das Sapucaias into a veritable death-trap and there seems to be no way of escape for the damned who are confined inside it in search of paradise!
name: Delirio!

description: Mister No has an account to square with Francisco Paco Medina, aka Abacaxi. No sooner had he once more set foot in Manaus after his last lengthy journey than Medina, a smuggler and a scoundrel involved in all sorts of crooked dealings, offered Jerry a real dirty job. After our friend had declined to take it on, Medina sent his thugs to unleash a hail of gunfire against the Piper. All this happened some time ago, but Mister No is not the kind of guy who forgets!
name: Agguato al “Victoria”

description: Ninety-seven thousand five hundred and thirty-seven cruzeiros: a really huge wad of money! That’s what Jerry and Ulisses are demanding from Francisco Paco Medina, i.e. the wheeler-dealer known by the name of Abacaxi. On the “Victoria” the final act of Mister No’s revenge is almost ready, but a freak of fate is lying in wait on the waters of the Rio Madeira!
name: Un Bel Mucchio di Cruzeiros

description: Mister No travels towards Rio Branco, in the Acre region of Brazil, in search of a friend whose whereabouts he lost track of some time ago. Mister No got an opportunity to make this trip because a new client of his, Att. Meurisse, wants to open a legal practice precisely in that area, which is completely off the beaten path, so that he can defend the downtrodden peasants who are browbeaten by their overlords. But our two friends are unaware that the welcome awaiting them down there is based on red-hot lead!
name: La Foresta Brucia!

description: In the Brazilian region of Acre the smouldering standoff between the seringueiros and the big landowners continues: there are too many interests at stake and, as usual, it’s the weakest ones who come off worst, even though the they’re supported by the experience of Att. Meurisse. In the fiery struggle that breaks out (liberally strewn with gunblasts but also with counterfeit documents), Mister No and Esse-Esse have already decided who to side with: they will defiantly challenge the powerful Burgama Company and its criminal bodyguards headed by Rudy Webber!
name: La Sfida di Esse-Esse

description: Att. Meurisse murdered, the Burgama Company’s forged documents that can no longer be contested, an increasingly tense stand-off between the poverty-stricken seringueiros and the armed militias of the big latifondista landowners, headed by Rudy Webber. And while Esse-Esse sets his revenge in motion, Mister No prepares to resist the destruction of the forest without brandishing a single weapon!
name: Empate!

description: After the bitter and dramatic epilogue of the adventure in the Acre region, Mister No and Esse-Esse return to Manaus, a city that has now changed so drastically that our friends can hardly recognize it as the place where they found shelter so many years ago. However, everyday life goes on monotonously – until, that is, Esse-Esse ends up getting embroiled in big trouble. And this time, in order to help him, Jerry will have to give in to loathsome blackmail!
name: La Festa è Finita

description: An expedition into the heart of the jungle in search of the Kamanau chief risks coming to an end in the worst possible way. Once again, Mister No finds himself guiding a group of men who perhaps conceal a dangerous secret. What really lies beneath the ruins of Mayarì, the ancient outpost of the Bureau of Indios Affairs? And who's prepared to go as far as to kill for the sake of getting their hands on it?
name: Missione Mayarì

description: Mister No agrees to act as a guide for an expedition that's planning to penetrate deep into the Amazon forest in search of chief Kamanau. The aim of the expedition organizers is to persuade the Waimiri-Atroari indios to allow a new "blade of concrete" to extend over their land. But the hazards of hostile nature and the ambushes of unscrupulous men slow down Jerry Drake's march, with daily hold-ups…
name: Alla Ricerca di Kamanau

description: Mister No and Taboka are continuing on their trip through the forest in search of Kamanau. But once he’s managed to avoid the tragic destiny his kidnappers were going to inflict on him, what unfolds before the Waimiri-Atroari chief’s eyes is the dramatic situation of his indios, decimated by a disease that seems to spell irremediable doom, while the white men are trying to get their hands on the indios’ lands. And with anguish in his heart, Kamanau will have to make an unspeakably awful decision…
name: La Roccia Rossa

description: The smoldering stand-off between Kamanau and his son Taboka, who are diametrically opposed on the issue of what to do about the road that’s going to cross the indios’ land, risks ending up tragically. And the fate of the Waimiri-Atroaris is sealed before Mister No’s very eyes. At the end of this dramatic adventure, the return to Manaus is disturbed by a strange unsettling apparition… What lies concealed beneath the masque of the monster that haunts the murky brine of “Black Lagoon”?
name: Black Lagoon

description:
Little Odessa

Mister No is in Little Odessa, the neighbourhood where the Russian community of New York gather and where the only law is that of the terrible “Organizatja”, the Russian Mafia, led by the ferocious Ptacek…

L'angelo della morte

Death comes from above! A serial killer shoots from the roofs of New York at defenceless passers-by. He shoots, kills, and then disappears in to thin air. Only Mister No will be able to stop him!

Il segno dei tre K

Harlem. At the Savoy the splendid Mara Jane Philips is performing. The attractive Afro-American singer receives threats from strangers, and Mister No and Phil Mulligan have to protect her. Maybe the strangers are men from the Ku Klux Klan, that has already killed her father, or perhaps the matter is more complicated and more ominous…
name: Little Odessa / L'Angelo della Morte / Il Segno dei Tre K

description: Manhattan, 1936. In the New York of the Great Depression, a restless young boy called Jerry Drake is growing up. He is the lucky mascot for the gigantic “Train” Kovalsky, the greatest street boxer of the day. And he is dangerously fascinated by the gangster Frankie “Messacantata” Nigro, who is his coach. Will Jerry become an “honest boy” like him?
name: C'Era Una Volta a New York

description:
Flip-book issue.

Shares its pages with Stan Winston's "Realm of the Claw".

Trakk came into a world bathed in blood. He travels the scorched remains of the earth to find the Helmet of Kyldran, rumored to hold the very balance between good and evil. Others -- some not of this world -- seek its awesome power as well. On this ruined planet, hope is the most precious gift of all, and a timeless warrior can only be saved by the subtleties of his own humanity. Desolation and despair have become the currency of this new world, trumped only by mayhem and death. For the few survivors of the last great war, the once sprawling city now affectionately known as "the Pit" has become the center of activity. Alien and mutant warlords flood the streets selling their wares -- human cattle and wholesale slaughter. The Pit seems all but lost until the arrival of a stranger from across the Dune Seas. As a special added bonus the start of Realm of The Claw is also featured as a back up story, which introduces a world where ancient legends of Gods and Goddesses collide with that of our own.
It's a flip-book, sharing its pages with Stan Winston's "Mutant Earth".

The same man who reorganized the previous Rocket Team for self-centred purposes has appeared in Ecruteak City, bringing down Tin Tower. In order to stop further damage, Gold and Silver meet the masked man at Lake of Rage for a battle. However, both of them disappeared after they were defeated by an overwhelmingly strong masked man. In the same Kanto area, Blue has become the gym leader of Viridian City while Red and Yellow set off for a journey in Johto. And at the same time, a girl is starting her own new adventures...
